post_text:
Hello Bulldog families!
We just wanted to get some information out to our families as we prepare for the new school year. As of right now we are in desperate need of volunteers to fill board seats. We are seeking someone to step in and take over as president, as our current president has filled that seat for the allocated number of consecutive year, per our bylaws. We also need at least 2 more people to step in and fill the other seats, be that as secretary, treasurer or vice president.
We will be working out the details of how meetings will look in the coming weeks.
The PTA has done some great work over the last couple of years, with the help of our fantastic parent volunteers! Please help keep this organization moving forward by volunteering your time. Together we can continue to make great progress!
Please message us here on Facebook or at byerspto@gmail.com.
Thank you and enjoy these last few days of summer break!

post_text:
Tonight we will be discussing a few changes.

*Our loyal Treasurer of the last year has moved out of State to pursue career advancement opportunities.

The PTA is looking for leaders!

Do you have fresh ideas to enhance our children’s educational experiences? Do you like to get involved and meet new people?

Byers School PTA is looking for a parent to fill the following position for 2019-2021 school year:
• Treasure

Treasurer Responsibilities
Please consider volunteering! If you have any questions about the positions, you can contact Shatzie Wardall
email Byerspto@gmail.com

Brief description of Treasurer duties
*Please see bylaws for full description.

Serve as custodian of the PTA’s finances, collect revenue, pay authorized expenses, follow all financial policies of the PTA, and hold all financial records. Monthly and report all financial activity monthly. The PTA shall arrange a review of its financial records each year.

Announcements will be sent out The PTA will be holding an election in the near future.

Please stay posted
